    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-08-20T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-08-20T18:00:00-05:00" n="594"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d594">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00112 European War 1939/6443: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé at Tangier</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Childs</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tangier</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-08-21T00:00:00+01:00"
                            >August 21, 1942—midnight</date>.<lb/>[Received August 22—10:55
                        a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>350. From the point of view of our own negotiations we can see no possible
                    objection to the proposal made in Madrid’s 1149, August 10 [<hi rend="italic"
                        >20</hi>]. Inasmuch as Orgaz himself has stated that he has referred our
                    proposal to his Government it is quite probable that he would welcome the
                    assurances suggested by the Ambassador, particularly if there appears to be any
                    such suspicion on the part of the Madrid Government as that mentioned in the
                    telegram under reference.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Tangier [<hi rend="italic">Madrid?</hi>].</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Childs</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
